## Marriage Rules (19-25)

**Dowry** (mahr): the groom pays a dowry to the bride, and it belongs to **her**. Not her father, not her family. *Her*. She can do whatever she wants with it.

> *"Give women their dowries as a free gift. But if they, of their own good pleasure, remit any part of it to you, take it and enjoy it."* (4)

**You cannot inherit women against their will** (19). In pre-Islamic Arabia, when a man died, his son or brother could "inherit" his widow like property, marrying her or preventing her from remarrying. The Quran bans this.

**Who you cannot marry** (23-24): your mothers, daughters, sisters, aunts, nieces, mother-in-law, stepdaughters (if you've consummated the marriage with their mother), two sisters at the same time, and women already married to someone else.

